node.text: When Brooke and Breanna Bennett learned that some girls miss school because they lack access to the period products they need, they decided to do something about it. They started @wit.womenintraining - an organization aimed at ending period poverty by providing period products to young people who cannot afford them, advocating for legislative change championing other social issues to help empower young women. The Always team donated 20,000 pads to help their cause and recognized them as one of their Period Heroes in October 2020. Thanks to our partner @katiecouric for sharing their story! #LeadWithLove
